This paper discusses the design and performance of wireless communication networks that are powered by wireless power transfer technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the joint wireless information and power transfer, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the challenges in designing an efficient WPCN, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the use of microwave wireless power transfer technology, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the future research directions for WPCN, which can be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
